# Developing Auto


## AI assistant



```bash
cat PROMPT.md

find . -type d \( -name ".git" -o -name "__pycache__" -o -name ".pytest_cache" -o -name "build" -o -name "dist" -o -name "bin" -o -name "lib" -o -name "assets" \) -prune -o -type f \( -name "*.py" -o -name "*.yaml" -o -name "*.yml" -o -name "*.sh" -o -name "Makefile" -o -name "*.txt" -o -name "*.md" -o -name "*.cnf" -o -name "*.spec" \) -exec printf '\n\n================================================================================\nFILE: {}\n================================================================================\n' \; -exec cat {} \;

tree -I 'bin|lib|.git|__pycache__|*.pyc'
```


## Deployment

We use github actions to create an exec file.  You can trigger that by pushing
a new tag version to the repo.

```bash
git tag -a vX.Y.Z -m "Release version vX.Y.Z"  # notice the `v` because it's important
git push origin --tags
```
